properties.name: Community Information
properties.webBody:
This Community Information message is being issued for Anglers Rest. 

  • This Community Information replaces the Advice message issued on April 2 at 11.30am. 
  • The bushfire at Anglers Rest is now contained.
  • Firefighters will continue attending to this fire. 
  • The Omeo Highway is open with speed restrictions remaining in place.  
  • This Community Information will be the last message for this bushfire.
There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required.   


This message was issued by DEECA.

The next update is expected by 03/04/2024 06:00 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires).
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.  
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.name: Community Information
properties.webBody:
This Community Information message is being issued for Strathmerton, Ulupna. 

  • There are multiple fires burning within Ulupna Island which are now under control.
  • Firefighters and machinery are attending to these fires.
  • Firefighters will be on scene for up to a week.
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby communities and roads.
  • This Community Information replaces the Community Information issued at 8:28pm Sunday 31 March 2024.
There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required.
This message was issued by Forest Fire Management Victoria.

The next update is expected by 05/04/2024 04:40 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires).
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.  
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.
